NPTrust Donor Advised Funds






















Donor-Advised Funds
Donor-advised funds are the most popular giving vehicle in philanthropy and NPT is the largest national independent provider. We offer donor-advised funds that are tailored to meet the needs of:
 
 
 
Why National Philanthropic Trust?
Our mission is to increase philanthropy in society. As a result, we offer donor-advised funds that are uniquely flexible:
NPT accepts the widest range of assets of any charitable organization.


Cash
Publicly traded securities including stocks, bonds, mutual fund shares
Restricted and controlled stock
Privately-held stock
Real estate
Proceeds from life insurance or from a full-paid policy


Transfers and grants from private foundations
Bequests from wills
Named beneficiary of charitable remainder trust
Named beneficiary of an IRA, 401(k), or other retirement account
Tangible personal property

 

NPT can make international grants and other types of specialized grants.


Endowing chairs at universities
Securing naming rights to buildings and programs


Establishing scholarship programs
Structuring multi-year, matching and challenge grants

 

NPT offers a wide range of investment options.


Blackrock iShares Russell 1000
Prudential Jennison 20/20 Focus
JP Morgan Mid Cap Value
Janus Enterprise Fund Class T
T. Rowe Price Diversified Small Cap Growth Fund
Fidelity Advisors Small Cap Value
American Century International Core Equity Fund
WCM Focused International Growth Fund
Federated International Small-Mid Company


Aberdeen Emerging Markets Fund
Baron Emerging Markets Fund
Fidelity Advisors Emerging Markets
Western Asset Core Fund


Loomis Sayles Core Plus Bond Fund 
Calvert Ultra-Short Bond Fund
Prudential Global Real Estate
Principal Diversified Real Asset
UBS Select Government Institutional Fund
iShares MSCI EAFE Optimized ETF
iShares MSCI ACWI Low Carbon Target ETF
iShares Sustainable MSCI Global Impact
iShares MSCI KLD 400 Social ETF

 

NPT allows you to identify successors or charitable beneficiaries so that your donor-advised fund can exist in perpetuity.

Learn More
For general questions about NPT donor-advised funds, please visit our FAQ section. For detailed questions about policies or procedures, please review the forms and instructions located in the "Who We Serve" sections of this website. If you would like to speak to someone about your philanthropic needs, please send us an email or call us toll free at (888) 878-7900.




