The Charles Schwab Family of Funds - Schwab Government Money Fund: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 27, 2017 9:55 AM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of The Charles Schwab Family of Funds - Schwab Government Money Fund



Snapshot People




Company Overview
The Charles Schwab Family of Funds - Schwab Government Money Fund is an open ended fixed income mutual fund launched and managed by Charles Schwab Investment Management, Inc. It invests in the money markets of United States. The fund primarily invests in government securities including Treasury bills, notes and repurchase agreements with an effective maturity of no longer than 397 days. The Charles Schwab Family of Funds - Schwab Government Money Fund was formed on January 26, 1990 and is domiciled in the United States.


211 Main StreetSan Francisco, CA 94105United StatesFounded in 1990



Phone: 415-667-9200

Fax: 415-667-1430

www.csimfunds.com/public/csim/home/products/mutual_funds/summary.html?symbol=SWGXX







