The Charles Schwab Family of Funds - Schwab Money Market Fund: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 27, 2017 9:55 AM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of The Charles Schwab Family of Funds - Schwab Money Market Fund



Snapshot People




Company Overview
The Charles Schwab Family of Funds - Schwab Money Market Fund is an open ended fixed income mutual fund launched and managed by Charles Schwab Investment Management, Inc. It invests in the money markets across the globe. The fund primarily invests in money market securities including commercial paper, including asset-backed commercial paper, promissory notes, certificates of deposit and time deposits, variable- and floating-rate debt securities, bank notes and repurchase agreements. It benchmarks the performance of its portfolio against the London Interbank Offered Rate Index. The Charles Schwab Family of Funds - Schwab Money Market Fund was formed on January 26, 1990 and is domiciled in the...
The Charles Schwab Family of Funds - Schwab Money Market Fund is an open ended fixed income mutual fund launched and managed by Charles Schwab Investment Management, Inc. It invests in the money markets across the globe. The fund primarily invests in money market securities including commercial paper, including asset-backed commercial paper, promissory notes, certificates of deposit and time deposits, variable- and floating-rate debt securities, bank notes and repurchase agreements. It benchmarks the performance of its portfolio against the London Interbank Offered Rate Index. The Charles Schwab Family of Funds - Schwab Money Market Fund was formed on January 26, 1990 and is domiciled in the United States. 
Detailed Description


211 Main StreetSan Francisco, CA 94105United StatesFounded in 1990



Phone: 415-667-9200

Fax: 415-667-1430

www.schwab.com







